{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{Use British English|date=February 2016}} '''Edward Hussey''' (c.1748 – 4 July 1816) was an English [[cricket]]er who played for [[Kent county cricket teams|Kent]].
He was educated at [[Westminster School|Westminster]] and lived at [[Ashford, Kent|Ashford]] in [[Kent]]. He had a long but infrequent career as a useful batsman and seems to have been a stalwart of Kent cricket, sometimes perhaps as a patron. His first known game was in 1773 and his last in 1797.
==External links== * {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010153250/http://www.jl.sl.btinternet.co.uk/stampsite/cricket/ladstolords/1771.html#hussey |date=10 October 2012 |title=From Lads to Lord's – profile }}
