'''Harrison Carlyon''' (born 23 January 2001) is a [[Jersey cricket team|Jersey]] international cricketer.<ref name="Bio">{{cite web |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/1062706.html |title=Harrison Carlyon |accessdate=7 June 2015 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> In October 2016 Carlyon was selected for Jersey's squad for the [[2016 ICC World Cricket League Division Four]] in [[Los Angeles]].<ref name="Squad">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/37618881 |title=Harrison Carlyon: Jersey pick 15-year-old for World Cricket League tournament |accessdate=1 November 2016 |work=BBC Sport}}</ref> He played in Jersey's first fixture of the tournament against [[Oman national cricket team|Oman]].<ref name="Oman">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/37803010 |title=World Cricket League: Jersey lose to Oman in opening game |accessdate=1 November 2016 |work=BBC Sport}}</ref><ref name="Scorecard">{{cite web |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/1062499.html |title=ICC World Cricket League Division Four, Jersey v Oman at Los Angeles, Oct 29, 2016 |accessdate=1 November 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> At the age of fifteen, he became the youngest player to represent Jersey in an international cricket match, breaking the previous record held by teammate [[Jonty Jenner]].<ref name="Youngest">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/37833609 |title=Harrison Carlyon: Jersey 15-year-old achieves international cricket 'dream' |accessdate=1 November 2016 |work=BBC Sport}}</ref>

In the final match for Jersey in the Division Four tournament, the fifth-place playoff against [[Italy national cricket team|Italy]], he played alongside his father and team manager, [[Tony Carlyon]].<ref name="fifthplace">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/1062513.html |title=ICC World Cricket League Division Four, 5th Place Playoff: Italy v Jersey at Los Angeles, Nov 5, 2016  |accessdate=6 November 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> Injuries in the Jersey team forced his father to play, becoming the first father and son to play together in an international match for Jersey.<ref name="USA-win">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/wcl-championship-2015-17/content/story/1064984.html |title=USA holds off Oman to claim WCL Division Four title |accessdate=6 November 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref><ref name="FatherSon">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/37870303 |title=World Cricket League Four: Relegated Jersey beat Italy as father and son make history |date=6 November 2016|accessdate=6 November 2016|work=BBC Sport}}</ref>

In April 2018, he was named in Jersey's squad for the [[2018 ICC World Cricket League Division Four]] tournament in Malaysia.<ref name="WCL-Div4">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/cricketinjersey/status/981515595777757184 |title=The 14 man national squad travelling to Malaysia |date=4 April 2018 |accessdate=4 April 2018 |work=Jersey Cricket Board}}</ref><ref name="JerEP">{{cite web|url=https://jerseyeveningpost.com/sport/2018/04/05/chuggys-men-for-mission-to-malaysia/ |title=Chuggy's men for mission to Malaysia |date=5 April 2018 |accessdate=6 April 2018 |work=Jersey Evening Post}}</ref> In August 2018, he was named in Jersey's squad for the [[2018–19 ICC World Twenty20 Europe Qualifier]] tournament in the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/45171461 |title=Jersey name squad for World Twenty20 first-round qualifier |work=BBC Sport |accessdate=13 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icc-cricket.com/news/808096 |title=Three debutants in Jersey squad for ICC World T20 Europe Qualifier |work=International Cricket Council |accessdate=14 August 2018}}</ref>

