{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Hatton Park | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Wellingborough]], [[Northamptonshire]] | establishment = 1873 <small>(first recorded match)</small> | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1874 | club1 = [[United North of England Eleven]] | date = 1 September | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/820.html Ground profile }}
'''Hatton Park''' was a [[cricket]] ground in [[Wellingborough]], [[Northamptonshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1873, when Wellingborough played a [[United North of England Eleven]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/820_misc.html Other matches played on Hatton Park]</ref> It was a [[United North of England Eleven]] that played a [[United South of England Eleven]] in the grounds only [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/820_f.html First-Class Matches played on Hatton Park]</ref> The final recorded match held on the ground came in 1884 when [[Northamptonshire County Cricket Club|Northamptonshire]] played [[Essex County Cricket Club|Essex]].
