The '''Ligi Ndogo Grounds''' are a series of [[Association football|football]] pitches in [[Nairobi]], [[Kenya]]. The dimensions of the main pitch stand at 100 [[Metre|m]] × 68 m (109 [[Yard|yd]] × 74 yd).

==History==
Formerly called the Unga Grounds, the grounds have been the home [[Ligi Ndogo S.C.|Ligi Ndogo]] since 2002 and its professional team since 2005. Situated on a 4-acre plot, the grounds hosted the first [[Ligi Ndogo S.C. Academy|Ligi Ndogo Academy]] season in January 2002, and as such is also home to its youth squads. The team's club house also stands at the grounds.

The Planets' first ever match was played on 13 June 2005 against [[Kariobangi Sharks F.C.|Kariobangi Sharks]], before proceeding to [[Manchester]], [[England]] for the [[Keele International Cup|Umbro International Cup]]. The Sharks beat the Planets 5–0. Their first ever [[Kenyan Nationwide League|Nationwide League]] match was played against Kuwinda in 2006, in which the Planets won 7–1.

==Other events==
The ground has been home to the annual Ligi Ndogo East Africa Tournament that includes teams from all [[East Africa]]n countries. In 2008 it briefly hosted the Ligi Ndogo Inter-centre tournament.

==Location==
Ligi Ndogo is located along [[Ngong Road]]. It is {{convert|6.4|km|mi}} from [[Nairobi]]'s [[central business district]].

