{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Victoria Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Leeds]], [[Yorkshire]] | coord = {{coord|53.8256|-1.5350|display=inline}} | establishment = 1846 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1872 | club1 = [[United North of England Eleven]] | date = 22 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/571.html Ground profile }}
The '''Victoria Ground''' (also known as the '''Royal Park''') was a [[cricket]] ground in [[Leeds]], [[Yorkshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1846, when a Yorkshire team played the [[William Clarke's All-England Eleven|All-England Eleven]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/571_misc.html Other matches played on Victoria Ground]</ref> The ground also hosted a single [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match in 1858 when the [[United North of England Eleven]] played the [[United South of England Eleven]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/571_f.html First-Class Matches played on Victoria Ground]</ref>
The final recorded match on the ground saw Leeds play the United North of England Eleven in 1878. The original size of the ground had decreased in 1858 when a portion of it was sold to a new owner and by 1890 the entire ground had been sold to be built upon. The exact location of the ground remains unknown.
